cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.CL, cs.LG. 

The paper discusses text indexing and information retrieval systems, which are typically categorized under cs.IR. However, the paper also focuses on exploiting non 1NF features of Object-Relational DBMS, which falls under cs.DB. The use of different database representations for better compression and faster query evaluation can also be categorized under cs.DS. Additionally, the paper deals with natural language processing and text analysis, which can be categorized under cs.CL. Finally, the paper reports detailed experimental results, which can be categorized under cs.LG.
